Remember to allow the dog to come to you.

Stay calm and confident. Then claim your space.

The dog will then come to you and eventually relax in front of you. This is the time to give the dog affection.

A dog learns Nose, Eyes, and Ears.

It is important to practice No Touch, No Talk, No Eye Contact!

Cesar Millan: Better Human Better Dog premieres Friday at 9/8c on National Geographic. @natgeotv 

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining #trainingtiptuesday

In this episode, I help a couple whose German Shepherd won't calm down.

The couple is 6 months pregnant and wants to prepare their German shepherd for their child.

Watch how I am able to address this issue and be sure to stay tuned for my new show premiering July 30, 2021 on National Geographic. 

Remember if you control the nose of a dog you control 60% of the brain.

We use food to demonstrate how to create rules, boundaries, and limitations.

It is crucial to develop these rules around food.

Calm and Confident.

Full Video on YouTube!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

#betterhumanbetterplanet
